article.description:
A healthy Jamal Mashburn is turning the Charlotte Hornets into serious contenders in the Eastern
Conference.
article.headline: Mashburn hits for 36 as Charlotte drills Indiana

images.name: Mashburn_Jamal 020324 inline
images.caption: Charlotte's Jamal Mashburn, right, and his 36 points were too much for Reggie Miller and Indiana to handle.

article.linkText: A healthy Mashburn leading Hornets to new heights
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- A healthy Jamal Mashburn is turning the Charlotte Hornets into serious contenders in the Eastern Conference. Mashburn matched a season high with 36 points and Baron Davis added 21 points and 11 assists as the Charlotte Hornets beat Indiana 99-84 Sunday and moved past the Pacers in the Eastern Conference playoff race. Charlotte moved into sole possession of seventh place in the conference with the victory. The Hornets extended their winning streak to six, the longest in the East, and went 3-1 against the Pacers this year. The Hornets are close to full strength after Mashburn (42 games), George Lynch (37) and David Wesley (15) all missed considerable time with injuries. Since Mashburn returned Feb. 18, the Hornets are 11-7 and three games over .500 for the first time this season. "When we're healthy, that gives us a chemistry that's incredibly important this time of year," Mashburn said. "It's better to be adding people to your team than deleting pieces like Philadelphia or Milwaukee." Charlotte saw its 19-point halftime lead cut to 11 by the end of the third period. Indiana's Jermaine O'Neal scored six consecutive points in the fourth, pulling the Pacers to 80-78 with 7:17 left. After a free throw by Charlotte's Jamaal Magloire, Mashburn took over. He hit consecutive baseline jumpers to push the lead to 85-78. Indiana's Austin Croshere made a layup, slicing Charlotte's lead to five, but Mashburn made two free throws to extend the lead to 87-82. The Hornets sealed the victory with a game-ending 8-1 run. "Mash was carrying us," Hornets coach Paul Silas said. "I thought he was a little tired, so I gave him a rest and that's when they made their run. The rest really helped us down the stretch. He came in and made some great hoops for us." Magloire had 14 points and 10 rebounds, P.J. Brown added 10 points and 19 rebounds and Robert Traylor finished with 10 points. Reggie Miller led the Pacers with 24 points. Jermaine O'Neal had 23 points and 11 rebounds. O'Neal went 8-for-24 from the floor, and the Pacers shot 34 percent. Mashburn opened the third quarter with a 3-pointer before the Pacers went on a 16-4 run to pull to 63-56. Mashburn then scored six of eight Charlotte points, stretching the lead to double digits. The Hornets led 75-64 at the end of the third. Miller and Ron Artest, who scored 11, hit consecutive baskets at the start of the fourth to make it 75-68. Miller was called for his third personal foul, followed by a technical, allowing Stacey Augmon to make two free throws for a 77-68 lead. O'Neal and Miller answered with baskets, but Davis, who was out of the lineup since picking up his fourth foul late in the third, came off the bench and hit a 3, extending the lead to 80-72. O'Neal, who scored 10 points in the fourth, spun around Traylor and hit a short jumper in the paint, cutting the lead to 80-78. Pacers coach Isiah Thomas said the Hornets are the most complete team in the East, and the one he'd least like to play in the playoffs. "Right now, they're just better than we are," he said. "They do it all. They've got all the pieces to make it work and experience to match." The Hornets aren't completely healthy. Elden Campbell missed his second consecutive game with a pulled right hamstring. Still, the Hornets say they're ready for the game Wednesday against Orlando, the third-place team in the East. "We've got our team intact and we're playing super basketball," Silas said. "We're not really that concerned with anybody in the East right now. We just want to make it. We like our chances against anybody." Game notes
Indiana's Brad Miller sat out with a sore left groin. ... Mashburn also scored 36 against New Jersey on Feb. 27. ... Five technical fouls were called. Indiana's Miller, Jamaal Tinsley and O'Neal were whistled for technicals. One was called on Charlotte's Brown. ... The Hornets had the other one on a defensive three-second violation. ... Croshere made his first start of the season in place of Brad Milller. He scored six points in 19 minutes. ...Pacers center Primoz Brezec, who had played only five minutes in the last 10 games, had four fouls and two points in 10 minutes.
